1. Use PyJWT as the library support:
    https://pyjwt.readthedocs.io/en/stable/
2. To install package
    pip3 install -r requirements.txt
3. Generate a public/private key pair
    https://blog.miguelgrinberg.com/post/json-web-tokens-with-public-key-signatures
    > openssl genrsa -out ./jwt_key.pem 2048
    > openssl rsa -pubout -in ./jwt_key.pem -out ./jwt_key_pub.pem
4. Use decorater to declare which route need to enforce JWT auth
5. Reference tutorial
    https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J5bIPtEbS0Q

6. HTTP authorization header
